This paper is about object detection using a neural network, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using multiple receptive fields and weakly-supervised segmentation, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-off between precision and speed, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE).
